═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  CACHE_READ WEIGHT TRANSITION: Does the Data Support a 0x → 1x Shift?
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

── SECTION 1: COUNTERFACTUAL ──────────────────────────────────────────

  Strongest evidence up front. Under the old formula (cache_read = 0x),
  how many days in our dataset would have exceeded the 180M 5h budget?
  Under the new formula (cache_read = 1x), how many days exceed?

  Month | Active Days | Days > 180M quota(0x) | Days > 180M quota(1x)
  ------|-------------|-----------------------|----------------------
  Feb   |          26 |                     0 |                    1
  Mar   |          31 |                     0 |                   11
  Apr   |          11 |                     0 |                    6
  ------|-------------|-----------------------|----------------------
  Total |             |                     0 |                   18

  Under the old formula, our maximum quota consumption in any single 5h
  window across the entire dataset was well below budget. The transition is
  not subtle — it's a categorical flip from "never constrained" to
  "constrained on most active days."

── SECTION 2: CACHE_READ SHARE HAS ALWAYS BEEN 90–95% ─────────────────

  Usage pattern didn't change. What changed is whether the quota system
  APPLIES cache_read weight.

  Month    | CacheRead     | % of Visible | Quota(0x)   | Quota(1x)   | Multiplier
  ---------|---------------|--------------|-------------|-------------|----------
  2025-12  |        407.6M |        95.7% |       20.7M |      428.4M |      20.7x
  2026-01  |       2538.0M |        91.8% |      231.4M |     2769.5M |      12.0x
  2026-02  |       1934.5M |        90.2% |      219.1M |     2153.6M |       9.8x
  2026-03  |       4443.8M |        92.9% |      394.2M |     4838.0M |      12.3x
  2026-04  |       2050.8M |        94.3% |      150.1M |     2200.9M |      14.7x

── SECTION 3: @fgrosswig 64x TEST ─────────────────────────────────────

  @fgrosswig (Max 5x): March 26 consumed 3.2B tokens with no limit.
  April 5 consumed 88M and hit 90%. A ~64x effective budget reduction.
  A 64x multiplier requires cache_read ≈ 98.4% of visible tokens.

  Our top 5 days by visible tokens (old-budget proxy):
    2026-04-01: 374.9M visible, 3080 calls, ratio=18.9x
    2026-03-23: 372.6M visible, 4107 calls, ratio=17.8x
    2026-04-11: 366.2M visible, 1129 calls, ratio=31.0x
    2026-03-21: 356.2M visible, 2796 calls, ratio=13.1x
    2026-03-17: 337.9M visible, 4985 calls, ratio=12.0x

