── KEY FINDINGS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Counterfactual: 0 days exceed 180M under quota(0x),
     18 days exceed under quota(1x). The old formula never bound us;
     the new formula does, on most active days.

  2. The 1x/0x ratio doesn't "jump" — it's 10–15x every week since Dec
     because cache_read has always been 90–95% of visible tokens.
     What changed is whether the quota system APPLIES the weight.

  3. The multiplier tells you how much worse each day becomes once
     cache_read counts. A 15x multiplier means the same workload now
     costs 15x more quota than before the change.
